cs.FL, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.GT

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with state complexity of regular languages and automata.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as the paper involves combinatorial arguments and proofs.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper deals with the complexity of regularity-preserving binary operations on regular languages.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper involves analyzing the state complexity of automata.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also a less likely category, but possible as the paper involves proving tight upper bounds on the state complexity of overlap assembly, which can be seen as a game between two automata.
